# Pull Request Template

When creating a pull request, use this format for the title and body.

## Title

- Short, imperative phrase (e.g. `Add Docker Compose setup`, `Fix booking overlap validation`)
- No period at the end


## Description

Summarize the changes and related issue. Include the motivation, context, and any implementation details reviewers need to understand the approach.

If the work closes an issue, include the appropriate reference:

`Resolves DEM2-<number>`

For GitHub issues, use:

`Fixes #<number>`

## Type of change

- [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking change that fixes an issue)
- [ ] New feature (non-breaking change that adds functionality)
- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that changes existing behavior)
- [ ] Documentation update

## How has this been tested?

Describe the tests run to verify the changes and provide enough detail for reviewers to reproduce the results.

- [ ] `make lint`
- [ ] `make test`
- [ ] `make build`

Add relevant manual verification steps, such as running `make dev` and exercising the affected flow.

## Checklist

- [ ] My code follows the style guidelines of this project
- [ ] I have performed a self-review of my changes
- [ ] I have added comments only where the logic is not obvious
- [ ] I have updated relevant documentation
- [ ] My changes generate no new warnings
- [ ] I have added or updated tests that prove the change works
- [ ] New and existing tests pass locally
- [ ] Any dependent changes have been merged and published

## Optional additions

- If schema or seed data changed, note that `database/schema.sql` and `backend/scripts/seed.ts` were updated together.
- For UI changes, include a `## Screenshots` section with before-and-after images when possible.
- Remove checklist items that do not apply, or mark them as not applicable with a brief explanation.

## Creating the PR

```bash
gh pr create --title "<title>" --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Description

Summarize the changes, motivation, context, and related issue.

Resolves DEM2-<number>

## Type of change

- [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking change that fixes an issue)
- [ ] New feature (non-breaking change that adds functionality)
- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that changes existing behavior)
- [ ] Documentation update

## How has this been tested?

Describe the tests run and how reviewers can reproduce the results.

- [ ] `make lint`
- [ ] `make test`
- [ ] `make build`

## Checklist

- [ ] My code follows the style guidelines of this project
- [ ] I have performed a self-review of my changes
- [ ] I have added comments only where the logic is not obvious
- [ ] I have updated relevant documentation
- [ ] My changes generate no new warnings
- [ ] I have added or updated tests that prove the change works
- [ ] New and existing tests pass locally
- [ ] Any dependent changes have been merged and published

EOF
)"
```

Create pull requests as ready for review by default.
